-- Tax Cut to Save Chinese Car Owners $476 Million, Xinhua Reports
-- B y   L i z a   L i n
-- 2012-02-14T13:49:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-14/tax-cut-to-save-chinese-car-owners-476-million-xinhua-reports.html
China ’s new vehicle tax will ease
the tax burden for owners of small- and medium-sized passenger
cars by 3 billion yuan ($476 million) in its first year,
according to a Xinhua story posted on the government’s website.  The new rates, in place since Jan. 1, cut taxes for
passenger vehicles with engines of between 1.0 liter and 1.6
liters in size by about 17 percent, Xinhua said. Taxes on
vehicles with engines smaller than 1.0 liter drop by at least 29
percent, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Liza Lin in Shanghai at 
